{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> κέντρον</b>, τό, <br /> (κεντέω) <b>any sharp point</b>: <br /><Level3><b>__1</b></Level3> <b>horse-goad</b>, [ἵπποι] ἄνευ κέντροιο θέοντες [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.387, compare 430, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1297, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 7.1.29, etc.; διπλοῖς κέντροισι 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 809; ὄνειδος ἔτυψεν δίκαν διφρηλάτου μεσολαβεῖ κ. 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 157 (Lyric poetry): post- 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], <b>ox-goad</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"(8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus βουπλήξ)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], used as an instrument of torture, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.130; κέντροις καὶ μάστιξιν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 777a: proverbial, πρὸς κέντρα λακτίζειν (see. λακτίζω 2); δεῖ.. κέντρου πολλάκις, οὕτω δὲ καὶ χαλινοῦ 3rd c.AD: Longinus Rhetor 2.2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; as a symbol of sovereignty, λαβὼν.. χερσὶν κέντρα κηδεύει πόλιν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 683. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <br /><Level4><b>__1.b</b></Level4> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>goad, spur, incentive</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “Fragmenta.” 124.4, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 691 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ποῦ γὰρ τοσοῦτο κ. ὡς μητροκτονεῖ; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Eu.” 427; κέντροις ἔρωτος 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 39, compare 1303; πόθου κ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 573a; κέντρα καὶ ὠδῖνες [prev. author] “Phdr.” 251e; κ. ἐγερτικὸν θυμοῦ 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Lycurgus” 21 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κέντρα πτολέμοιο, of the Argives, Oracle texts cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"Scholia 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 14.48 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; κ. ἐμοῦ <b>desire for</b> me, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 1039. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, in <i>plural</i>, <b>tortures, pangs</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Tr.” 840 (Lyric poetry): _sing._, τὸ κ. τοῦ θανάτου ἡ ἁμαρτία NT.1Cor.15.56. \">NT</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <b>point</b> of a spear, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 6.22.4: _plural_, of the περόναι\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>] with which Oedipus pierced his eyes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1318. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> <b>peg</b> of a top, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 436d. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__5</b></Level3> of animals, <br /><Level4><b>__5.a</b></Level4> <b>sting</b> of bees and wasps, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 225, 407 (Lyric poetry), +others\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of scorpions, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Partibus Animalium” 683a12 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>] (so of the constellation [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Scorpio”, 4th-3rd c.BC: Aratus Epicus 505)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: hence, <i>metaphorically</i>, of malicious persons, ἐς τοὺς ἔχοντας κέντρ᾽ ἀφιᾶσιν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 242; πορεύεται, ὥσπερ σκορπίος, ἠρκὼς τὸ κ. 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 25.52 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of Pericles as an orator, τὸ κ. ἐγκατέλειπε τοῖς ἀκροωμένοις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Eupolis Comicus 94.7 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of Socrates, ὥσπερ μέλιττα τὸ κ. ἐγκαταλιπών [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 91c; οἷον ὀφθαλμῷ κ. ἐνθεῖσα 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Philostrati majoris imagines” 2.1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; βλέμματος κ. Onomarch. cited in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Philostratus Sophista “Vitae Sophistarum” 2.18. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] <br /><Level4><b>__5.b</b></Level4> <b>spur</b> of a cock, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Geoponica” 14.7.17. \">Refs</a>] <br /><Level4><b>__5.c</b></Level4> <b>quill</b> of the porcupine, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Aelianus “De Natura Animalium - Ar.Byzantine Epit.” 12.26. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>] <br /><Level4><b>__5.d</b></Level4> ={πόσθη}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Sotades Lyricus 1. \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__6</b></Level3> <b>stationary point of a pair of compasses</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Vitruvius Scriptor de Architectura Latinus 3.1.3\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]: generally, <b>centre</b> of a circle, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 54e, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Analytica Priora” 41b15, +others\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἡ ἐκ τοῦ κ. (i.e. εὐθεῖα) <b>radius</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Euclides Geometra “Optica” 34; ὥσπερ κύκλον κέντρῳ περιέγραψαν τὴν πόλιν 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Romulus” 11; τὸ κ. τᾶς σφαίρας 5th-4th c.BC: Timaeus Locrus Philosophus 100e; τὸ κ. τῆς γῆς 2nd c.AD: Ptolemaeus Mathematicus “Tetrabiblos” 52 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κ. βάρεος <b>centre</b> of gravity, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Archimedes Geometra “περὶ ἰσορροπιῶν” 1 “Def.” 4: _metaphorically_, κ. καὶ διαστήματι περιγράφειν\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>] <b>circumscribe</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.513c, 524f. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level